Package entity

Class FlatBooking

java.lang.Object
entity.FlatBooking
public class FlatBooking extends Object
The FlatBooking class represents a booking made by an applicant for a housing flat. It contains details such as the applicant's personal information, the flat's location and type, the selling price, and the project associated with the booking.

      public FlatBooking(String applicantName, String applicantNRIC, int applicantAge, String applicantMaritalStatus, String projectName, String flatType, String neighborhood, int sellPrice)
      Constructs a new FlatBooking with the given details. The booking ID is automatically generated.
      Parameters:
      applicantName - the full name of the applicant
      applicantNRIC - the NRIC of the applicant
      applicantAge - the age of the applicant
      applicantMaritalStatus - the marital status of the applicant
      projectName - the name of the housing project
      flatType - the type of flat booked (e.g., 3-room, 4-room)
      neighborhood - the neighborhood of the flat
      sellPrice - the selling price of the flat

    • FlatBooking

      public FlatBooking(int bookingID, String applicantName, String applicantNRIC, int applicantAge, String applicantMaritalStatus, String projectName, String flatType, String neighborhood, int sellPrice)

      Parameters:
      bookingID - the manually assigned booking ID
      applicantName - the full name of the applicant
      applicantNRIC - the NRIC of the applicant
      applicantAge - the age of the applicant
      applicantMaritalStatus - the marital status of the applicant
      projectName - the name of the housing project
      flatType - the type of flat booked
      neighborhood - the neighborhood of the flat
      sellPrice - the selling price of the flat
